Wideawake
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the nickname given by Maoris to Colonel William Wakefield, the NZ Company's Wellington agent: an alteration of or play on <i>Wake</i>field, with reference to his headgear, and possibly to the fact that he was an alert or devious businessman
Origin:[none]
